          "id": 2,
          "question": "<p><a name=\"25014\"></a><div itemprop=\"text\"><p>In how many different ways can \\( r \\) elements be picked from a set of \\( n \\) elements if</p>\n\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:lower-roman\">\n\t<li>&nbsp;Repetition is not allowed and the order of picking matters?</li>\n\t<li>&nbsp;Repetition is allowed and the order of picking does not matter?</li>\n</ol>\n\n</div><br><br><b>Combinatory: TIFR CSE 2012 | Part A | Question: 10</b></p>",
          "type": "single",
          "options": [
            "<p>\\( \\frac{n!}{\\left(n - r\\right)!} \\) and \\( \\frac{\\left(n + r - 1\\right)!}{r!\\left(n - 1\\right)!} \\), respectively.</p>",
            "<p>\\( \\frac{n!}{\\left(n - r\\right)!} \\) and \\( \\frac{n!}{r!\\left(n - 1\\right)!} \\), respectively.</p>",
            "<p>\\( \\frac{n!}{r!\\left(n - r\\right)!} \\) and \\( \\frac{\\left(n - r + 1\\right)!}{r!\\left(n - 1\\right)!} \\), respectively.</p>",
            "<p>\\( \\frac{n!}{r!\\left(n - r\\right)!} \\) and \\( \\frac{n!}{\\left(n - r\\right)!} \\), respectively.</p>",
            "<p>\\( \\frac{n!}{r!} \\) and \\( \\frac{r!}{n!} \\), respectively.</p>"
          ],
          "correct_answer": "<p>\\( \\frac{n!}{\\left(n - r\\right)!} \\) and \\( \\frac{\\left(n + r - 1\\right)!}{r!\\left(n - 1\\right)!} \\), respectively.</p>",
